===Etymology===
From {{etyl|es|en}} {{term|anchova|lang=es}}, from [[Genoese]] {{etyl|lij|en}} or from {{etyl|co|en}}. The term's ultimate origin is unclear; some suggest it may have derived from an unattested {{etyl|VL.|en}} term {{recons|apiuva|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|aphye|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἀφύη|lang=grc}}; others suggest it comes from {{etyl|eu|en}} {{term|anchu||dried fish|lang=eu}}, from {{term|anchuva||dry|lang=eu}}.<ref>{{R:Etymonline}}</ref>

